Working on this at the moment: <a href="http://pimpanalytics.ga/" rel="nofollow">http://pimpanalytics.ga/</a> Make your Google Analytics stand out with Pimp Analytics. Put any 7 letter isogram in the input boxes below and create your own custom GA snippet. From Wikipedia&#x27;s article on isograms: &quot;An isogram (also known as a &#x27;nonpattern word&#x27;) is a logological term for a word or phrase without a repeating letter&quot;. Enter non-repeating alphabet [a-z] letters. Note: uppercase letters will be automatically transformed to lowercase. Note: Entering numbers will break your code as per the JS syntax. Inspired by this blogpost:<p><a href="http://blog.higg.im/2015/03/17/tinkering-with-the-google-analytics-js-snippet-a-lesson-in-isograms/" rel="nofollow">http://blog.higg.im/2015/03/17/tinkering-with-the-google-ana...</a><p>I even dogfood the service in the source code:<p><pre><code>	 (function (m,a,c,k,i,n,g) {
     m[&#x27;GoogleAnalyticsObject&#x27;] = i;
     m[i] = m[i] || function () {
         (m[i].q = m[i].q || []).push(arguments)
     }, m[i].l = 1 * new Date();
     n = a.createElement(c),
     g = a.getElementsByTagName(c)[0];
     n.async = 1;
     n.src = k;
     g.parentNode.insertBefore(n, g)
     })(window, document, &#x27;script&#x27;, &#x27;//www.google-analytics.com/analytics.js&#x27;, &#x27;ga&#x27;);
     ga(&#x27;create&#x27;, &#x27;UA-66070213-3&#x27;, &#x27;auto&#x27;);
     ga(&#x27;send&#x27;, &#x27;pageview&#x27;);
</code></pre>
Check it: <a href="http://pimpanalytics.ga/" rel="nofollow">http://pimpanalytics.ga/</a>
